 class="t m118a x11 h2b yf3f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in bondage to them which by nature are no gods ; but now that </div><div class="t m21dc x11 h2b y18e2 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ye have come to know God, or rather to be known of God, how </div><div class="t m1647 x11 h2b y18e3 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">turn ye back again to the weak and beggarly rudiments, where-</div><div class="t m21e8 x11 h2b y1370 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">unto ye desire to be in bondage over again ? Ye observe days, </div><div class="t mf68 x11 h2b y11e4 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and months, and seasons, and years. I am afraid of you, lest by </div><div class="t mae6 x11 h2b y1316 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">any means I</div><div class="t m212f x3f h2b y1316 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-</div><div class="t m93c x35 h2b y1316 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">have bestowed labor upon you in vain.&quot; </div><div class="t mb74 x14 h2b y1111 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be sure that you have -the preceding verses clearly fixed in </div><div class="t m1588 x11 h2b y118f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">your mind, before you proceed with these, and then note the con-</div><div class="t mc48 x11 h2b y1505 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nection. If those have been well learned, it will be no task, but-</div><div class="t m841 x11 h2b y98d ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">a pleasure, to include them in the present lesson. </div><div class="t m317 x47 h2b y1090 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">QUESTIONS. </div><div class="t m494 x5d h2b y1091 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In what condition were we all in former times ? </div><div class="t mbf2 x5d h2b y1508 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;In bondage under the rudiments of the world.&quot; </div><div class="t m7b4 x5d h2b yeeb ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What are the rudiments of the world ? See i John 2 : 15, i6; </div><div class="t m21f5 x11 h2b y1f64 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eph. </div><div class="t m1b11 x29 h5f y1f4d ff4 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 : </div><div class="t m81b x5d h2b y150a ff4